"title": "4125: Satan, agents of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4125",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Satan works in this world through people and through those spiritual beings who acknowledge his authority. His agents oppose God's will and purposes.</p>\n<h2>Satan works through people</h2>\n<h3>Satan's human agents pursue his evil desires</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:44\">JHN 8:44</a></strong> <em>Jesus Christ speaking of the relationship of some unbelieving Jews to Satan.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:10\">ACT 13:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:8-1John3:10\">1JN 3:8–3:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:12\">1JN 3:12</a></p>\n<h3>Satan works through people to oppose God's purposes</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:1-Acts5:9\">ACT 5:1–5:9</a> <em>Ananias and Sapphira</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:23\">MAT 16:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:33\">MRK 8:33</a> <em>Simon Peter</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:3\">LUK 22:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:70\">JHN 6:70</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:2\">JHN 13:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:27\">JHN 13:27</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:8-Acts13:10\">ACT 13:8–13:10</a> <em>Elymas, the sorcerer</em></p>\n<h2>Examples of people doing Satan's work</h2>\n<h3>False prophets</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut13:5\">DEU 13:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:26-Jer23:27\">JER 23:26–23:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer28:15\">JER 28:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer29:21\">JER 29:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek13:6-Ezek13:9\">EZK 13:6–13:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:15\">MAT 7:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:24\">MAT 24:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:1-2Pet2:3\">2PE 2:1–2:3</a></p>\n<h3>Others who lead people away from God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut13:13\">DEU 13:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:9-2Kgs21:26\">2KI 21:9–21:26</a> <em>Manasseh and his son, Amon</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:21\">PRO 7:21</a> <em>the adulteress</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:12\">ISA 3:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:6\">JER 50:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:18-2Pet2:19\">2PE 2:18–2:19</a></p>\n<h2>Satan works through his spiritual agents</h2>\n<h3>Satan's angels</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:41\">MAT 25:41</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:4\">2PE 2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:7\">REV 12:7</a> <em>“angel” and “messenger” are the same word in Greek</em></p>\n<h3>Satan's demons</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:11-Luke13:16\">LUK 13:11–13:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:22\">MAT 12:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:14-Luke11:15\">LUK 11:14–11:15</a></p>\n<h2>Satan's agents are identified by various images and titles</h2>\n<h3>The little horn</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan8:9-Dan8:12\">DAN 8:9–8:12</a> <em>This probably represents Antiochus Epiphanes.</em></p>\n<h3>The prince of Persia</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan10:13\">DAN 10:13</a> <em>probably representing a demon with influence over the Persian kingdom</em></p>\n<h3>The king of the North</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan11:28\">DAN 11:28</a> <em>probably representing Antiochus Epiphanes</em></p>\n<h3>The antichrist</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:1-1John4:4\">1JN 4:1–4:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2John1:7\">2JN 1:7</a></p>\n<h3>The man of lawlessness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:3-2Thess2:10\">2TH 2:3–2:10</a></p>\n<h3>The beast</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev11:7\">REV 11:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:1-Rev13:8\">REV 13:1–13:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:11-Rev13:18\">REV 13:11–13:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:9-Rev14:11\">REV 14:9–14:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:13\">REV 16:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:8\">REV 17:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:20\">REV 19:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:10\">REV 20:10</a></p>\n<h3>The false prophet</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:13\">REV 16:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:20\">REV 19:20</a></p>\n<h3>The prostitute or Babylon the Great</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:8\">REV 14:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:19\">REV 16:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:1-Rev17:18\">REV 17:1–17:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:1-Rev18:10\">REV 18:1–18:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:18\">REV 18:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:2\">REV 19:2</a></p>",
